	   <tr><td colspan=2>Once again, the famous.. (What weaps should I be using, what slots, and why?)... question.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of now at level 51, I have the following weapons in inventory:<br><br>Locustlure - 8dmg 17dly proc Walking Sleep (slow spell) 1.3wt<br><br>Bloodpoint (2each) - 10dmg 21dly +5str -5cha +10sv poison/disease proc 80hp lifetap 2.3wt<br><br>Intricate Silver Rapier - 13dmg 27dly +5ac +15cha 1.5wt<br><br>As of now, I am using the Locustlure in primary untill the proc is iniciated, then switch to the rapier in primary for huge BS and hits, with a Bloodpoint always in 2ndary.  When my hps are below 3 bubs of health, I stay with a bloodpoint in each hand for the lifetap procs, making sure to evade after each proc to ensure no agro.<br><br>I am sure these weapons shall be efficient till I get my ragebringer.  But I still can't help wondering if I am using my weapons effectively.  Oh yeah, just to ensure my 1hs is up to par, I keep a Hammered Velium Warsword (11dmg 24dly) in my back pocket.  Thanks for ur suggestions in advance.<br>&nbsp;<br>Baroness Sleeque<br>60 Backstabbing<br>Klepto-Locksmith<br>Eastern Keep Guild<br>Rodcet Nife Server</td></tr>
